iderat der Forschung war. Er berücksichtigt die Erkenntnisse der philologischen, theologischen und mediävistischen Forschung der letzten Jahrzehnte.  aPrudentius’ Psychomachia is the first fully allegorical epic in the Western tradition. It was an especially important reference for the art and literature of the middle ages. As the first commentary on this work from late antiquity, Magnus Frisch’s book is an important contribution to the field. The commentary also takes into account relevant recent research in the areas of philology, theology, and medieval studies.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aPrudentius. 4aspätantike christliche Dichtung. 4aspätantikes christliches Epos. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aChristian epic.  aChristian poetry.  aPrudentius.  alate antiquity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020z9783110704631oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311062843240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311063083140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110630831423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110630831/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020